# Kiosk Design System (iFCM)

All interfaces must match the self-service kiosk visual language. Source of truth: `shared/styles.css` (tokens in `:root`) and `shared/global.css` (utilities).

## Palette (strict)

| Token | Value | Usage |
|-------|-------|-------|
| `--color-navy` | `#1E1B4B` | Primary buttons, prices, headings |
| `--color-danger` | `#E11D48` | Cancel, destructive actions |
| `--color-bg` | `#F3F4F6` | Page background |
| `--color-text-muted` | `#6b7280` | Secondary text, labels |

Never use `#1A3B6E`, orange accent, or ad-hoc colors.

## Typography

- Font: `Montserrat` via Google Fonts
- Headings/CTAs: `font-weight: 700–800`, `letter-spacing: 0.03–0.06em`, `text-transform: uppercase` for section titles and primary buttons
- Prices: `font-weight: 800`, `color: var(--color-navy)`, `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums`

## Components

- **Cards**: `border-radius: 16px`, `box-shadow: var(--shadow-card)`
- **Primary CTA**: navy pill (`border-radius: 9999px`), `box-shadow: var(--shadow-btn-navy)`, class `btn btn-primary btn-pill btn-press`
- **Cancel**: white + rose border (`btn-outline-danger`)
- **Tabs/switchers**: pill container, active segment = navy fill (see `.auth-tabs`, `.cat-tab`)
- **Footers**: sticky bottom bar with `box-shadow: var(--shadow-footer)`
- **Touch feedback**: always add `btn-press` on interactive elements

## Imports

```js
import '../shared/global.css'; // includes styles.css tokens
import './style.css';
```

HTML: include Montserrat from Google Fonts (see `client-lk/index.html`).

## Layout & spacing (UI/UX)

- Interface must feel **airy, clean, modern** — avoid cramped layouts.
- **Spacing grid**: multiples of 4px/8px. Use tokens: `--space-sm` (8px), `--space-md` (16px), `--space-lg` (24px).
- **Form blocks**: inputs must never stick to buttons or neighbors. Minimum gap between form sections — **16–24px**.
- **Label → input**: `--space-sm` (8px). **Between form groups**: `--space-md` (16px). **Last input → CTA button**: `--space-md` + `--space-sm` = **24px**.
- Use flex/grid containers with explicit `gap`, not margin hacks on individual fields.
- **Touch targets**: inputs and buttons `min-height: 44–48px` on mobile.

### Form pattern

```html
<div class="auth-fields"> <!-- or .form-stack -->
  <div class="form-group">...</div>
  <button class="btn btn-primary btn-pill">Submit</button>
</div>
```

```css
.auth-fields { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-md); }
.auth-fields .btn { margin-top: var(--space-sm); } /* +8px → 24px before CTA */
.form-group { gap: var(--space-sm); }
```

## Premium Wallet Card (ID card)

Unified digital wallet card for client LK: food card number, balance, history link, and QR on one tactile surface. **Reference:** `client-lk/pages/home.js`, `client-lk/style.css` (`.lk-id-card` … `.id-card-qr`).

### When to use

- User identity / food card / balance summary in client LK
- Any “show QR at checkout” block that must feel premium and match primary CTAs

### Structure

```html
<div class="lk-id-card">
  <div class="id-card-surface">
    <div class="id-card-pattern" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="id-card-content">
      <div class="id-card-info">
        <div class="id-card-details" role="button" tabindex="0">
          <div class="id-card-label">Карта питания:</div>
          <div class="id-card-number">BD4PSTZYSKC4</div>
          <div class="id-card-balance-row">
            <span class="id-card-balance-label">Баланс:</span>
            <span class="id-card-balance">330,00 ₽</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <button class="id-card-history-link btn-press" type="button">Смотреть историю заказов &gt;</button>
      </div>
      <button class="id-card-qr btn-press" type="button" aria-label="Показать QR-код">
        <img src="…" alt="QR-код" />
      </button>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
```

### Surface & color (strict)

- **Background:** rich navy gradient — same family as `btn-primary`, never gray or violet/purple tints
  - `#35317f → #28256a → var(--color-navy) → var(--color-primary-dark)`
- **Gloss:** `::before` white sheen + navy radial highlights; `::after` subtle corner bloom — all `rgba(30, 27, 75, …)` or navy-tinted
- **Shadow:** layered floating shadow `rgba(30, 27, 75, 0.18–0.52)` — stronger than `--shadow-card`
- **Pattern:** `.id-card-pattern` — white SVG food icons, `opacity: 0.07`, `background-size: 120px`
- **Shape:** `border-radius: 20px`, `padding: 22px 20px`, `overflow: hidden`

### Typography (on card)

| Element | Size | Weight | Color |
|---------|------|--------|-------|
| Label («Карта питания:») | `--font-size-xs` | 400 | `rgba(255,255,255,0.72)` |
| Card number | `--font-size-sm` | 400 | `#fff`, `letter-spacing: 0.02em` |
| «Баланс:» | `--font-size-xs` | 400 | `rgba(255,255,255,0.72)` |
| Amount | `--font-size-xs` | 600 | `#fff`, tabular-nums |
| History link | `--font-size-sm` | 500 | `rgba(255,255,255,0.62)` → `#fff` on hover |

No balance pill/bubble — amount is plain text on the card surface.

### QR chip

- White container on the right: `92×92px`, `border-radius: 14px`, `padding: 8px`
- `box-shadow: 0 6px 16px rgba(0,0,0,0.18)` + subtle navy inset border
- Flex row: `.id-card-content` with `gap: var(--space-lg)`, `align-items: center`

### Do / Don't

- ✅ Reuse existing class names; copy styles from `client-lk/style.css`
- ✅ Keep history link inline under balance, not a separate gray block
- ❌ Gray or slate backgrounds on the card surface
- ❌ Purple/violet accent colors (`#5b4fd6`, indigo-500, etc.) — stay in navy token family
- ❌ Large bold card number — keep compact and light (400 weight)
